cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with the task of visual question answering for remote sensing data, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a system that uses automatic methods to extract information from remote sensing data, which involves machine learning techniques such as Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval techniques, as it queries information from OpenStreetMap (OSM), making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category.
